From 827a0d7564553c68f17d1daee5b901f2e3d26399 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: WPE Android downstream <wpe-android@igalia.com>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 11:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] wpewebkit: apply downstream Skia DDL patch for Mali GPU
 rasterization

Adds the developer-supplied Skia DeferredDisplayList patch
(`recipes/wpewebkit/0001-...`) as a downstream patch and registers it
in the recipe.

The patch reroutes paint workers to record into a
GrDeferredDisplayList instead of issuing GL commands; the compositor
thread replays each DDL on its single GrContext. Eliminates the
cross-context GL race that produces tile-edge seams, black tile
corners, and post-scroll wrong-content blocks on Mali (Pixel 7) when
the Skia compositor is used with GPU rasterization. Pairs with the
BGRA atlas fix added in the previous commit.

Held downstream until the upstream is available.
